Defendant Gustavo Adolfo Gonzalez Estrada in court with Attorney Karl Huebner.  ADA Theresa Beck in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Attorney Huebner indicates that the parties have a plan for First Offender Program participation, however the Court has not approved this.  
ADA Beck provides a summary of the FOP intended oversight and monitoring.
The Court indicates that it will sign the proposed order approving the First Offender Program.
 
Attorney Huebner orally renews the Defense request to have the contact prohibition condition of Bond dropped. 
ADA Beck indicates that when a defenant is in the FOP, the State would like for the FOP Coordinator Ms. McCoy to weigh-in on such a request, and also the assigned prosecutor. ADA Beck proposes that the Court have the parties discuss this further and possibly submit a written stipulation to modify Bond.  
The Court continues the no contact bond prohibiiton in the Bond.

Defendant Gustavo Adolfo Gonzalez Estrada appears in court.  Public Service Special Prosecutor Melanie Flint appears for the State of Wisconsin.

Mr. Gonzalez Estrada indicates that he is asking that the Court appoint an attorney for him.  
The Court requires Mr. Gonzalez Estrada to go to the Clerk of Courts Office to fill out the petition for appointment of counsel.
The Victim is present in the courtroom. The Victim voices a request that the Court lift the contact prohibition; the Victim wishes for Mr. Gonzalez Estrada to be able to have contact.
The Court denies this bond modification request.  The Bond and conditions of Bond are reviewed.
